header.gameNote: SPORTSTIME OHIO BCA CLASSIC AT COLUMBUS OH

article.headline: IUPUI 86, Alabama A&M 47
article.story: COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- George Hill scored 20 points and Austin Montgomery added 15 and IUPUI went on a 27-7 run in the first half en route to an 86-47 victory over Alabama A&M in the opening round of the BCA Classic at Ohio State University on Friday. Hill hit all five of his first half shots and scored 15 points in the first half for the Jaguars (1-0). Montgomery added 10 points. IUPUI scored 35 points off 27 turnovers by Alabama A&M, including 15 in the first half. The Jaguars shot 49 percent, 27-of-55, from the field to 38 percent, 17-of-45 for Alabama A&M (0-1). Angelo Smith, Craig Swope and Gary Patterson scored nine points apiece for IUPUI. Evan Hilton led Alabama A&M with 15 points and Cornelius Hester scored eight.
